title: Gloucester Harbor, from Harper's Weekly, September 27, 1873, p. 844
medium: Wood engraving in black ink on newsprint paper.
description: Horizontal view showing in the foreground seven boys sitting in and on dories moored side by side, while in the background a number of sailboats in full sail coursing through harbor.  Information from David Tatham's Winslow Homer and the Pictorial Press (Syracuse, NY: Syracuse University Press, 2003).
name: Print
